cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with bibliometrics and citation-rank indicators. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the analysis of citation data. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as citation networks are a type of social network. It could also be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the evaluation of scientific research. Finally, it may be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as citation-rank indicators are sometimes used in the evaluation of security research.
